        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 8 at 10:34PM CDT until July 8 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Wheeler County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Hemphill County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 1115 PM CDT.

* At 1033 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles north of
Allison, or 21 miles southeast of Canadian, moving south at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

* Locations impacted include...
Briscoe, Wheeler, and Allison.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
